    "asOf": "2003-03-19",
    "date": "2006-11-28T17:35:40Z",
    "text": "Repeals: (1) Federal law governing the transportation of mail by surface carrier, including law authorizing the U.S. Postal Service to obtain mail transportation service from common carriers by rail and motor vehicle; and (2) restrictions on the length of Postal Service contracts for the transportation of mail.Prohibits the Postal Service from telling a contractor, either directly or indirectly, how, when, or where to purchase services and supplies, including fuel and equipment."
